  "headline_html": "<ul><li><b>Single-expiry median AUM cap: $3.7M.</b> At the canonical EXP-1220 single-expiration Monday entry, the median Monday in 2020-2025 supports a book of $3.7M at 10% participation.</li><li><b>Top-3 staggered median AUM cap: $5.7M.</b> Spreading entries across the three highest-volume expiries in the 21-45 DTE window multiplies median capacity by <b>1.5\u00d7</b>.</li><li><b>Feasibility with top-3 staggering:</b> $100M is tradable on 3% of Mondays, $200M on 0%, $500M on 0%. A production staggered strategy could comfortably run a $1M book with almost no forced-downsize days (the p5-Monday capacity is the binding constraint).</li><li><b>AUM ceiling for 'always-tradable' (95%+ feasibility):</b> <b>single_expiry</b>=< $50M; <b>top2_expiries</b>=< $50M; <b>top3_expiries</b>=< $50M; <b>all_expiries</b>=< $50M; </li></ul>"
